Top command line utilities
top -- general statistics ---- "1" will list cpus out.
vmstat -- virtual memory statistics
lsof -- open files
   1. To list open files
   2. To list network ports
   3. Processes opening file: lsof /var/log/syslog
   4. Match processes with name: lsof -c ssh -c init
   5. by a process: lsof -p 1753
   6. network connections on port 80: lsof -i  :80
   7. by process: lsof -i -a -p 234   OR  lsof -i -a -c ssh
tcpdump -- dumps network traffic
   tcpdump -i eth0
   print out packets on ethernet card: tcpdump -A -i eth0
   display text in hex format and ascii:  tcpdump -XX -i eth0
   capture packets: tcpdump -w 0001.pcap -i eth0

